## Safety notice (non-license, informational)

This software actuates physical gates, doors and barriers. Its failure modes are
physical: a gate that fails to open during a fire, or opens for someone it shouldn't,
can hurt people.

- This software must never be the sole means of egress. Fire and building codes in
  most jurisdictions require code-compliant fail-safe mechanical or electrical
  release hardware on egress routes, independent of any access-control system.
  Install this software in parallel with that required hardware — never in series
  with it, and never as a replacement for it.
- The operator of any installation is responsible for compliance with local fire,
  building, safety and accessibility codes. Nothing in this software, or in this
  notice, determines what those codes require at a given site.
- The warranty disclaimer above ("AS IS", no warranty, no liability) is a standard
  MIT term limiting the authors' and copyright holders' liability. It does not
  excuse an incorrect installation, and it does not transfer the operator's legal
  duties to anyone else.
- The authors are not lawyers, and neither this notice nor the project's
  documentation is legal advice. Obtain your own legal/compliance review before
  deploying this software to control a real gate, door or barrier.

Questions or reports: vulosorg@gmail.com.
